-- Italian Police Arrest 60, Seize Assets in Anti-Mafia Operation
-- B y   L o r e n z o   T o t a r o
-- 2012-03-20T10:35:00Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-20/italian-police-arrest-60-seize-assets-in-anti-mafia-operation.html
Italian police arrested 60 people,
including 16 tax judges, and seized assets worth 1 billion euros
($1.32 billion) in an anti-mafia operation, authorities in
Naples said.  The arrests took place yesterday in the regions of
Campania, of which Naples is the capital, and in Lombardy,
northern  Italy , the tax police, Guardia di Finanza, said in an
e-mailed statement. Among the people arrested were 10 employees
of tax authorities of Naples, the police said.  Italian investigators working with Swiss police seized
property, businesses, bank deposits with a total value of 1
billion euros, the police also said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Lorenzo Totaro in Rome at 
